sentences: After moving to NYC in 2008, Etheridge signed to the Rock Ridge Music label.
His 2014 release "The Straight and Narrow Way" was recorded in Los Angeles, New Orleans and Nashville and “features a clash of musical influences, legends and genres.”
In August 2014 the band appeared in the 26th edition of the Blues to Bop Festival in Lugano, Switzerland to strong reviews.
Following the 2014 release, Etheridge toured the U.S. as support for Rock and Roll Hall of Fame artist Leon Russell.
Raised in Columbia, South Carolina, he spent twenty years in Louisiana before moving to New York City, where he currently resides.
Etheridge performed with a series of bands during his 20 years living in Baton Rouge, Louisiana including the country/Cajun group the River City Good Time Band.
“The Straight And Narrow Way” includes two duets with Sara Watkins (Nickel Creek) as well as support from guest vocalist Erica Falls (Joe Sample).
